The paper deals with wireless communication channels and their security aspects, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas and statistical knowledge of channel state information also suggests the sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes an iterative algorithm, which falls under the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
